# LocalTools Roadmap (living)

Last update: 2026-06-03
Scope: Next.js 16 SPA toolbox, 100% client-side, no backend/auth/tracking/uploads.

## Current Snapshot

- App shell + URL state (`?tool=<id>`) implemented.
- i18n modular (`en`/`es`) implemented.
- Theme persistence implemented.
- Central registry implemented: 32 tools in `src/modules/tool-registry/application/tools.ts`.
- Test suite present for multiple domain modules + shared form primitives.
- Existing planning doc present: `ROADMAP.md` (historical, long-form).

## Gaps Found

- Topbar tool search likely not fully wired (historical roadmap marks it as decorative).
- Final quality pass pending:
  - accessibility audit
  - performance/Lighthouse recertification
  - integration-level UI tests for key tools

## Active Phases

### Phase A - Tooling Baseline Hardening

Status: in progress

- Add `typecheck` script (`tsc --noEmit`). ✅
- Confirm local quality gate sequence:
  1. lint
  2. typecheck ✅
  3. test
  4. build ✅
- Align AGENTS workflow and scripts so closure checks are executable.

### Phase B - UX Completion

Status: pending

- Implement real topbar tool search behavior (if still placeholder).
- Validate keyboard-first navigation across sidebar/topbar/tool forms.
- Ensure consistent action UX (copy/clear/download/error) across all tools.

### Phase C - Quality Certification

Status: pending

- Run and document accessibility pass (WCAG 2.1 AA focus on primary flows).
- Run Lighthouse in release mode and capture baseline.
- Add/expand tests for high-usage interactive tools not yet covered at presentation level.

## Delivery Rules

- Update this file after each completed block with real status.
- Keep edits scoped; no unrelated refactors.
- Before closing technical task: run `bun run typecheck` (after script exists).
- Before closing major changes: run `bun run build`.

## Immediate Next Block

1. Replace native color pickers with shared modern picker.
2. Start notifications system migration (`sileo`).
3. Evaluate/integrate `@cmd-kit/react` where applicable.
4. Run `bun run typecheck` + `bun run build`.

